## STACK — READ THIS FIRST BEFORE SUGGESTING ANYTHING

- Vanilla HTML, CSS, and JavaScript only. No frameworks whatsoever.
- Deployed on Vercel via GitHub Desktop (no CLI workflow).
- Serverless functions live in /api/ and run as Vercel Edge/Node functions.
- Static pages are pre-generated via Node scripts (generate-mountain-pages.mjs,
  generate-state-pages.mjs) — they are not server-rendered at request time.
- No build step, no bundler, no npm for the frontend. Scripts are loaded via <script> tags.
- Node.js is only used for the static generation scripts and /api/ serverless functions.

NEVER suggest:
- React, Vue, Svelte, Angular, or any frontend framework
- Webpack, Vite, Parcel, or any bundler
- TypeScript (unless explicitly asked)
- npm packages for the frontend
- Replacing <script> tag imports with ES module bundling
- Rewriting existing working logic "for cleanliness"

