## KEY FILES — WHAT EACH ONE DOES

### Core Application
- sd-app.js         — Main application logic, UI rendering, questionnaire flow,
                       Top Pick card rendering, "Also in the Running" card rendering.
                       This is the largest and most sensitive file. Edit carefully.

- sd-scoring.js     — Personalization scoring algorithm. Takes user-selected weights
                       and scores each resort. The normalizedWeights() function is
                       CRITICAL — it must always return dynamic weights derived from
                       user input, never hardcoded fixed values. A previous bug where
                       it returned fixed weights regardless of input was a major failure.
                       Never touch normalizedWeights() without explicit instruction.

- sd-data.js        — Resort data loader. Uses vm.runInNewContext() to parse resort
                       data files because JSON.parse() silently fails on JS object
                       literal syntax. Do NOT change this parsing approach.

- resorts-national.js — Raw resort dataset. Contains all resort entries with stats,
                         pricing, coordinates, terrain data, etc. Data quality here
                         directly affects recommendation quality.

- featured-partners.js — Sponsor/partner integration. Controls Featured Partner
                          placements. The business model depends on this file being
                          clean and reliable.

### Static Page Generation
- generate-mountain-pages.mjs — Generates all 256 individual resort pages.
                                  Run with Node.js when resort data changes.
- generate-state-pages.mjs    — Generates all 34 state landing pages.

### Serverless Functions (/api/)
- /api/subscribe.js — Beehiiv email subscription handler. Reads
                       BEEHIIV_API_KEY and BEEHIIV_PUBLICATION_ID from
                       Vercel environment variables. Never hardcode these.

