## SCORING SYSTEM — NEVER BREAK THIS

The scoring system is the entire product. Two components must always stay in sync:

1. sd-scoring.js computes a normalized score (0–100) for each resort based on
   user-selected priority weights across dimensions like snow quality, terrain variety,
   value, family-friendliness, après ski, drive distance, etc.

2. sd-app.js uses those scores to:
   - Designate the highest-scoring resort as the TOP PICK
   - Designate the next 2–3 as "ALSO IN THE RUNNING"
   - Render verdict labels (e.g., "Best Overall Value", "Top Snow Resort")

A critical past bug: the scoring label system in sd-app.js was disconnected from the
actual numeric scores in sd-scoring.js, producing contradictory results (e.g., a resort
labeled "Best Value" with a low value score). This has been fixed. Any future edit to
scoring labels must reference actual computed score values, never hardcoded logic.

Rules:
- Never add a new scoring dimension without wiring it into BOTH sd-scoring.js AND sd-app.js
- Never change how normalizedWeights() aggregates user input without explicit instruction
- Always check: does the Top Pick label match what the score actually says?

