## SEO ARCHITECTURE — DO NOT BREAK

The site has a deliberate SEO content structure built for organic discovery:

Pages that exist and must stay intact:
- 256 individual resort pages (e.g., /resorts/killington-vermont.html)
- 34 state landing pages (e.g., /states/vermont.html)
- City landing pages (e.g., /from/boston.html, /from/new-york.html)
- Ski pass comparison hub (/passes/) + 5 regional comparison pages
- robots.txt at root
- sitemap.xml (must stay current — regenerate if new pages are added)

Canonical tag rules:
- Every page must have <link rel="canonical"> pointing to its own non-www URL
- The canonical domain is wheretoskinext.com (no www)
- Never create a page without a canonical tag

Navigation must be consistent across all page types. If you change the nav on one
template, flag that it needs to propagate to all templates.

