## CHANGE MANAGEMENT RULES

These rules exist because this codebase is maintained by a non-coder via AI tooling.
Safety is more important than elegance.

1. SCOPE LOCK — Only change what was explicitly asked. If you notice something else
   that could be improved, mention it in a comment at the end of your response.
   Do not fix it silently.

2. NO SILENT REFACTORS — Never rename variables, reorganize file structure, or
   change function signatures unless that was the explicit request.

3. EXPLAIN THE DIFF — For any change to sd-scoring.js or sd-app.js, include a
   plain-English explanation of exactly what changed and why, as if explaining to
   someone who doesn't code.

4. FLAG BLAST RADIUS — If a change to one file requires changes in another file
   to stay consistent, call this out explicitly before proceeding. Do not make the
   secondary change silently.

5. STATIC PAGE REGENERATION — If you edit resort data in resorts-national.js or
   change the page templates, remind the operator to re-run the generation scripts:
     node generate-mountain-pages.mjs
     node generate-state-pages.mjs
   and to redeploy via GitHub Desktop.

6. TEST THE CRITICAL PATH — After any change to the scoring or UI flow, the operator
   should manually test: load homepage → complete questionnaire → verify Top Pick
   card shows a resort with a label that matches its actual highest score dimension.

