## KNOWN PAST BUGS (never reintroduce these)

- normalizedWeights() returning hardcoded fixed weights instead of user-input-derived
  weights, making the personalization engine non-functional.
- JSON.parse() failing silently on JS object literal syntax in data files. Fixed by
  switching to vm.runInNewContext(). Do not revert this.
- Two disconnected scoring systems in sd-scoring.js and sd-app.js producing
  contradictory verdict labels. Fixed by unifying score references.
- Resort coordinates placed in wrong states. Always verify lat/lng when adding
  or editing resort entries.
- www vs non-www canonical mismatch causing duplicate indexing issues in GSC.
  All canonicals point to non-www. Vercel redirects www → non-www.

